2026-04-30T03:18:38.4966312Z             "body": "## Summary\nThis PR adds Docker containerization support to the project by introducing a Dockerfile and integrating automated Docker image building and pushing into the CI/CD pipeline.\n\n## Key Changes\n- **Added Dockerfile**: Multi-stage build configuration using .NET 8.0 SDK and ASP.NET runtime\n  - Builds the `Ednsv.Web` project in Release configuration\n  - Optimizes image size with separate build and runtime stages\n  - Exposes port 8080 and sets appropriate environment variables for containerized ASP.NET Core\n  \n- **Added .dockerignore**: Excludes unnecessary files from the Docker build context (build artifacts, IDE files, tests, cache files, etc.)\n\n- **Added Docker CI/CD job**: New `docker` workflow job in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`\n  - Depends on successful `build-and-test` job\n  - Builds and pushes Docker images to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR)\n  - Only pushes images on non-PR events (branches and tags)\n  - Generates multiple image tags: branch name, PR reference, short SHA, and `latest` for default branch\n  - Uses GitHub Actions cache for faster builds\n  - Requires `contents: read` and `packages: write` permissions\n\n- **Updated CI workflow**: Modified `push-build-logs` job to depend on the new `docker` job\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Docker image is published to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository }}`\n- Uses Docker Buildx for efficient multi-platform builds with caching\n- Authentication to GHCR uses `GITHUB_TOKEN` for secure, automatic credential management\n- Build context includes only necessary source files via `.dockerignore`\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01CgwAiqqRZZYVbe176CsWtN",
2026-04-30T03:18:38.4971973Z             "changed_files": 3,
